com.ibm.mobile.services.data

Interface IBMDataStorageProviderConnectCallback


  • public interface IBMDataStorageProviderConnectCallback
    The IBMDataStorageProviderConnectCallback class is a provisional API. APIs that are marked provisional are evolving and might change or be removed in future releases. Storage Provider client event interface.

    • Method Detail

      • onStorageConnected

        void onStorageConnected(IBMDataStorageProvider provider,
                      IBMDataConnectionParams params)
        The onStorageConnected method is a provisional API. APIs that are marked provisional are evolving and might change or be removed in future releases. Storage Provider connected successfully. From this point on the client application is free to connect to the Cloud Manager.
        Parameters:
        provider - IBMDataStorageProvider connected.
        params - ICLConnectionParams representation of the parameters passed during connection.

      • onStorageConnectError

        void onStorageConnectError(IBMDataStorageProvider provider,
                         IBMDataFileException error)
        The onStorageConnectError method is a provisional API. APIs that are marked provisional are evolving and might change or be removed in future releases. Invoked if there is any error during the connect process. The Storage Provider won't connect if this event is invoked.
        Parameters:
        provider - IBMDataStorageProvider connected.
        error - IBMDataFileException thrown.

      • onStorageDisconnected

        void onStorageDisconnected(IBMDataStorageProvider provider)
        The onStorageDisconnected method is a provisional API. APIs that are marked provisional are evolving and might change or be removed in future releases. Invoked after a successful disconnect.
        Parameters:
        provider - IBMDataStorageProvider disconnected.

      • onStorageDisconnectError

        void onStorageDisconnectError(IBMDataStorageProvider provider,
                            IBMDataFileException error)
        The onStorageDisconnectError method is a provisional API. APIs that are marked provisional are evolving and might change or be removed in future releases. Invoked if there is any error during the disconnect process. The client application should check if the Storage Provider is still connected.
        Parameters:
        provider - IBMDataStorageProvider with error.
        error - IBMDataFileException thrown.
